summary: This document appears to be a communication from AT&T regarding the inability to obtain location information for a mobile number associated with an investigation. It discusses potential reasons for the lack of data and emphasizes caution in using the provided location estimates for investigative purposes.
keyFacts: The document indicates that location information could not be obtained due to the mobile being powered off, out of service area, or in an area where location information is unavailable.
AT&T provides a confidence level for the location data, but warns that results may not be exact due to sourcing from various databases.
The document mentions that if no results were returned, AT&T has no available location information responsive to the request.
